<p>The degree variance is supposed to capture the extent to which there is =
inequality in the connectivity of nodes in a graph. Inequality exists when =
a few nodes have a lot of connections and most nodes only have a few. The m=
ore inequality, the higher the degree variance. This means that in graphs w=
here there is very little variation in the connectivity of each node (all n=
odes have roughly the same number of connections), the degree variance shou=
ld be at a minimum.</p>
</section>
