<h3 data-number=3D"10.8.3" class=3D"anchored" data-anchor-id=3D"node-averag=
e-nearest-neighbor-degree"><span class=3D"header-section-number">10.8.3</sp=
an> Node Average Nearest Neighbor Degree<a class=3D"anchorjs-link " aria-la=
bel=3D"Anchor" data-anchorjs-icon=3D"=EE=A7=8B" href=3D"https://olizardo.gi=
thub.io/networks-textbook/lesson-graphs-degree-metrics.html#node-average-ne=
arest-neighbor-degree" style=3D"font: 1em / 1 anchorjs-icons; padding-left:=
 0.375em;"></a></h3>
<p>Just in the same way we can compute the degree of each node, we may be i=
nterested in in the question of whether nodes in the network tend to connec=
t to others of high degree, or whether the connections in the network occur=
 at random, irrespective of degree. The first situation, where people tend =
to connect to other people of high degree is called <strong>preferential at=
tachment</strong> in network science <span class=3D"citation" data-cites=3D=
"barabasi_albert99">(<a href=3D"https://olizardo.github.io/networks-textboo=
k/lesson-graphs-degree-metrics.html#ref-barabasi_albert99" role=3D"doc-bibl=
ioref" aria-expanded=3D"false">Barab=C3=A1si and Albert 1999</a>)</span>. I=
t is also referred to as a <strong>popularity tournament structure</strong>=
 in sociology <span class=3D"citation" data-cites=3D"waller37">(<a href=3D"=
https://olizardo.github.io/networks-textbook/lesson-graphs-degree-metrics.h=
tml#ref-waller37" role=3D"doc-biblioref" aria-expanded=3D"false">Waller 193=
7</a>)</span>. If you went to a real live high school, you may know how thi=
s works.</p>
<p>To get a sense of whether a given node prefers to connect to others who =
also have a large number of connections, we can compute an index called the=
 <strong>average nearest neighbor degree</strong>, which is conventionally =
written <span class=3D"math inline"><mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMen=
u_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"75" style=3D=
"font-size: 119.6%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-h=
idden=3D"true"><mjx-msub><mjx-texatom texclass=3D"ORD"><mjx-mover><mjx-over=
 style=3D"padding-bottom: 0.105em; padding-left: 0.261em; margin-bottom: -0=
.544em;"><mjx-mo class=3D"mjx-n" style=3D"width: 0px; margin-left: -0.25em;=
"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-cAF"></mjx-c></mjx-mo></mjx-over><mjx-base><mjx-mi cl=
ass=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D458 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-base=
></mjx-mover></mjx-texatom><mjx-script style=3D"vertical-align: -0.177em;">=
<mjx-texatom size=3D"s" texclass=3D"ORD"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c cla=
ss=3D"mjx-c1D45B TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c cla=
